  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether hydration with sodium bicarbonate is more
      effective than hydration with sodium chloride to prevent contrast induced nephropathy in
      patients undergoing Primary Coronary Intervention for Acute ST Elevation Myocardial
      Infarction.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
